{"lemma":"غِرَّة","slug":"غِرَّة","root":"غ.ر.ر","root_slug":"غ-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31577","n31587","n31588"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"white spot, blaze"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the prime, the cutting edge, remoteness from the bad"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beginning, onset, outset"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"inadvertency, lack of particular attention or equipment"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣur.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31577","headword_ar":"غَرَّهُ","root":"gr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagur~u","text_ar":"يَغُرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guruwrN","text_ar":"غُرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~N","text_ar":"غَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az, K,) which latter is preferable to the former, [though less common,] because the inf. n. of a trans. verb is scarcely ever of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Az,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gir~apN","text_ar":"غِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gararN","text_ar":"غَرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the devil, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceived him; beguiled him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him to desire what was vain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"false."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~atohu Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"غَرَّتْهُ الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The world deceived him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beguiled him, by its finery,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"show,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pomp."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said in the Kur [lxxxii. 6],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA gar~aka birab~ika","text_ar":"مَا غَرَّكَ بِرَبِّكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What hath deceived thee, and led thee into error, so that thou hast neglected what was incumbent on thee to thy Lord?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Is-hák:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what hath deceived thee respecting thy Lord, and induced thee to disobey Him, and to feel secure from his punishment?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what hath deceived thee, and emboldened thee to disobey thy Lord?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd. [But see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA gar~aka bifulaAnK","text_ar":"مَا غَرَّكَ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What hath deceived thee, and emboldened thee against such a one?"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"how is it that thou art emboldened against such a one?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, Msb, TA.) [See also 4.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano","text_ar":"مَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~aka bifulaAnK","text_ar":"غَرَّكَ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Who hath made thee to pursue a course without being rightly directed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a course not plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^awoTaA^aka","text_ar":"مَنْ اَوْطَاَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$owapF","text_ar":"عُشْوَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to the case of such a one?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See again 4.]) [Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~a mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"غُرَّ مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~a guruwrFA SaAdirFA","text_ar":"غُرَّ غُرُورًا صَادِرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was deceived by such a one; he was deceived with deceit proceeding from such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gariyrN","text_ar":"غَرِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"magoruwrN","text_ar":"مَغْرُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a fulaAnN fulaAnFA","text_ar":"غَرَّ فُلَانٌ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one exposed such a one to perdition"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destruction"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by deceiving him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [See also 2, and 4.]) Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one acted with such a one in a manner resembling the slaying with the edge of the sword."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See 3 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ETw","text_ar":"عطو"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a faroxahu","text_ar":"غَرَّ فَرْخَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~N","text_ar":"غَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraArN","text_ar":"غِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, [or the latter is inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAr~a","text_ar":"غَارَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a bird, S, O, K, * or a pigeon, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fed its young one with its bill:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^unovaAhu","text_ar":"اُنْثَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gAr~","text_ar":"غارّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraArN","text_ar":"غِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mugaAr~apN","text_ar":"مُغَارَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the [collared turtle-dove called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumoriY~","text_ar":"قُمْرِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fed his female with his bill."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna yagur~u Ealiy~FA","text_ar":"كَانَ يَغُرُّ عَلِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlEilomi","text_ar":"بِالعِلْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the Prophet)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used to nourish 'Alee with knowledge like as the bird feeds its young one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA. *) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~a fulaAnN mina AlEilomi maA lamo","text_ar":"غُرَّ فُلَانٌ مِنَ العِلْمِ مَا لَمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yugar~uhu gayoruhu","text_ar":"يُغَرُّهُ غَيْرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one has been nourished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instructed, with that wherewith other than he has not been nourished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instructed, of knowledge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a","text_ar":"غَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagir~u","text_ar":"يَغِرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) with kesr; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a","text_ar":"غَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garirota","text_ar":"غَرِرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagar~u","text_ar":"يَغَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaArapN","text_ar":"غَرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, Msb, or a youth, or young man, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was inexperienced in affairs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was ignorant of affairs; negligent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heedless, of them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *`lika fiY garaAratiY waHadaAvatiY","text_ar":"كَانَ ذٰلِكَ فِى غَرَارَتِى وَحَدَاثَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY gir~atiY","text_ar":"فِى غِرَّتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the time of]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my inexperience and youth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See also 8.] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a","text_ar":"غَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) see. pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garrota","text_ar":"غَررْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, T, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagar~u","text_ar":"يَغَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, (IAar, T, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaArapN","text_ar":"غَرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted in a youthful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"childish manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he so acted after having soundness of judgment, produced by experience."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K.) But this is at variance with what J cites from Fr, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$d","text_ar":"شد"},{"kind":"text","text":", that the aor. of an intrans. verb of this class of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", should be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yafoEilu","text_ar":"يَفْعِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a","text_ar":"غَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, IKtt, K,) in one place written by IAar"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garira","text_ar":"غَرِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to show that it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEila","text_ar":"فَعِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that the sec. pers. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garirota","text_ar":"غَرِرْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagar~u","text_ar":"يَغَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, IKtt, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gararN","text_ar":"غَرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~apN","text_ar":"غُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, IKtt, K,) or the latter, as ISd thinks, is not an inf. n., but a subst., (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garAarapN","text_ar":"غَراَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse, IAar, IKtt, and a camel, IAar)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had what is termed a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~ap","text_ar":"غُرَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his forehead:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, IKtt:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(his face)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had what is so termed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(his face)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became white."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K. *) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a","text_ar":"غَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yagar~u","text_ar":"يَغَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became eminent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~apN","text_ar":"غُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also A grape-vine's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly becoming tall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A5-  See also R. Q. 1.       -A6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~a Ealayohi","text_ar":"غَرَّ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA='a","text_ar":"المَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He poured upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qar~a","text_ar":"قَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~a fiY HawoDika","text_ar":"غُرَّ فِى حَوْضِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pour thou into thy watering-trough."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~a fiY siqaAy^ika","text_ar":"غُرَّ فِى سِقَايِكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fill thou thy skin by putting it into the water and throwing the water into it with thy hand, not abstaining until thou fillest it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus as related by Az accord. to the usage of the desert-Arabs. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","S","Msb","K","Az","Lh","IKtt","TA","O","As","IAar","T"]},{"entry_id":"n31587","headword_ar":"غُرَّةٌ","root":"gr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whiteness: clearness of colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complexion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA.) So in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~apF","text_ar":"غُرَّةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agar~u","text_ar":"اَغَرُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most. fair-complexioned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; occurring in a trad. applied to virgins: or the phrase is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gir~apF","text_ar":"غِرَّةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agar~u","text_ar":"اَغَرُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most, remote from the knowledge of evil."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blaze,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white mark, on the forehead"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"face of a horse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a whiteness on the forehead of a horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above the size of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroham","text_ar":"دِرْهَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the size of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"drhm","text_ar":"درهم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurogurapN","text_ar":"غُرْغُرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a general term"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a star"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blaze"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"including different kinds, as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quroHap","text_ar":"قُرْحَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$imoraAx","text_ar":"شِمْرَاخ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if round, it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watiyrapN","text_ar":"وَتِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and if long,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAdixapN","text_ar":"شَادِخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or as, ISd thinks, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space itself, of the face, that is occupied by whiteness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not the whiteness: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurarN","text_ar":"غُرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agar~u","text_ar":"اَغَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  In a dog,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A white speck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small white spot, above each of the eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in a trad., in which it is said that the black dog having two such marks is to be killed. (TA.)       -A2-  Also (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the month; (Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the month,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the new moon is first seen:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) so called as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~ap","text_ar":"غُرَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the forehead of a horse: (AHeyth:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurarN","text_ar":"غُرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHeyth, Msb:) which is also applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first three nights of the month."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, Msb.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katabotu gur~apa Al$~ahori","text_ar":"كَتَبْتُ غُرَّةَ الشَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wrote on the first of the month thus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,] (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of El-Islám; (TA;) and of anything. (S.) ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whiteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the teeth; and the ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first that appears"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of them. (K.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when first appearing"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a plant. (TA.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spectacle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever appears to one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of light, or daybreak: you say thereof,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badato gur~atuhu","text_ar":"بَدَتْ غُرَّتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spectacle, thereof appeared"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aspect"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the new moon: (K:) because of its whiteness: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"phasis"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the moon"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the first night of the month"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"face"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man: (K:) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aspect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloEap","text_ar":"طَلْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)  [And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forehead"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man. So used, as opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qafFA","text_ar":"قَفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Life of Teemoor, 170, ed. Mang., cited by Freytag; and so used in the present day; but whether in classical times I know not.] ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTowiylu Algur~api","text_ar":"تَطْوِيلُ الغُرَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". in performing the ablution termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waDuwo'","text_ar":"وَضُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":", means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The washing of the fore part of the head with the face, and the washing of the side of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the washing of somewhat of the fore arm and of the shank with the hand and the foot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) ―         -b10-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~ahN","text_ar":"غُرَّهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eminent man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) of a people (S, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gurarN","text_ar":"غُرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b11-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and chiefest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) of goods. or household furniture: (K:) pl. as above: (TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything: (S:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most precious and excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed,) of property ; as, for instance,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an excellent camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed, Mgh.) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male slave."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed. S. Mgh, Msb, K.) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a female slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a clever female slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Sa'eed, Mgh:) its application to a slave, male or female, [among articles of property,] is most common. (TA.) It has this last signification (a male or female slave) in a trad. in which it relates to the compensation for the destroying of a child in the womb: (TA:) as though this term were applied, by a synecdoche, to the whole person; (S;) the word properly signifying the “ face; ” in like manner as the terms"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqabapN","text_ar":"رَقَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osN","text_ar":"رَاْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are employed: (Mgh:) Aboo-'Amr Ibn-El-Alà is related to have said that it there means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a white male slave"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a white female slave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but this is not a condition accord. to the doctors of practical law; for they hold the term to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female slave whose price amounts to the tenth part of the whole price of blood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the twentieth part thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, T:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a slave of the best sort."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) The Rájiz says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kul~u qatiylK fiY kulayobK gur~aho\n                      \n                     \n                        Hat~aY yanaAla Alqatolu A=la mur~aho"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every one slain in retaliation for Kuleyb is"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a slave, until the slaying reach the family of Mur-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2239},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rah."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b12-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iy~aAkumo waAlmu$Aar~apa faA_in~ahaA","text_ar":"اـِيَّاكُمْ وَالمُشاَرَّةَ فَاـِنَّهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadofinu Algur~apa watuZohiru AlEur~apa","text_ar":"تَدْفِنُ الغُرَّةَ وَتُظْهِرُ العُرَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Avoid ye contention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disputation, for it hides goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and manifests what is disgraceful"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A3-  [It is also an inf. n.: see 1, latter part.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","AHeyth","Msb","TA","Mgh","IAth","T"]},{"entry_id":"n31588","headword_ar":"غِرَّةٌ","root":"gr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Negligence; inattention; inadvertence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inadvertency; inconsiderateness; heedlessness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unpreparedness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gir~aAtN","text_ar":"غِرَّاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girarN","text_ar":"غِرَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see an ex. of the former in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afaEa","text_ar":"شَفَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and exs. of both in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daraY","text_ar":"دَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":".] It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algir~apu tajolibu Ald~ir~apa","text_ar":"الغِرَّةُ تَجْلِبُ الدِّرَّةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inadvertence brings the means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paucity of milk causes to come abundance thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to him who gives little and from whom much is hoped for afterwards. (Meyd. [See Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 179: and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"girAarN","text_ar":"غِراَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY gir~apK","text_ar":"عَلَى غِرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On an occasion of negligence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unexpectedly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErD","text_ar":"عرض"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano gir~apK","text_ar":"عَنْ غِرَّةٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In consequence of inadvertence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zalaqN","text_ar":"زَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inexperience in affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gir~apN","text_ar":"غِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garaArapN","text_ar":"غَرَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same. (A'Obeyd.) [The latter is an inf. n.: see 1.] See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gur~apN","text_ar":"غُرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", second sentence. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gir~apN biA@ll~`hi","text_ar":"غِرَّةٌ بِا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Boldness against God."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A2-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gir~N","text_ar":"غِرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]}]}}